<div class="headings">
    <div class="h2">Mammals</div>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div class="h3">Lions</div>
    <p>The king of the jungle, lions are majestic creatures known for their strength and leadership in their prides.</p>

    <div class="h3">Elephants</div>
    <p>These gentle giants are the largest land mammals and exhibit remarkable intelligence and social behavior.</p>

    <div class="h3">Giraffes</div>
    <p>With their long necks and unique spotted patterns, giraffes are fascinating animals that roam the African
        savannahs.</p>

    <hr>

    <div class="h2">Birds</div>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div class="h3">Eagles</div>
    <p>Eagles are magnificent birds of prey, known for their keen eyesight, soaring abilities, and powerful hunting
        skills.</p>

    <div class="h3">Hummingbirds</div>
    <p>These tiny birds captivate with their vibrant colors and astonishing agility, often appearing to hover in
        mid-air.</p>

    <hr>

    <div class="h2">Reptiles</div>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div class="h3">Turtles</div>
    <p>With their protective shells, turtles have been around for millions of years, representing longevity and
        resilience.</p>

    <div class="h3">Snakes</div>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div class="h4">Boa Constrictors</div>
    <p>Boa constrictors are non-venomous snakes that use their muscular bodies to constrict and overpower their
        prey.</p>

    <div class="h4">Rattlesnakes</div>
    <p>Rattlesnakes possess a distinctive rattle on their tail, warning potential threats with its characteristic
        sound.</p>
